To efficiently estimate MI in a high-dimensional setting, we build upon the manifold assumption [cayton:05:manifold-learning-algorithms], based on which embedding techniques were developed that successfully capture the most relevant information in few dimensions
by focussing on preserving local Euclidean distances and estimating geodesics that resemble the data location on the manifold [mcinnes:20:umap,vandermaaten:08:tsne,tenenbaum:00:isomap].